<item>
            <title>[LU-17249] protect scp_rqbd_idle list operations in ptlrpc_service_purge_all()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17249</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are evidences that list entry taken from &lt;tt&gt;scp_rqbd_idle&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;ptlrpc_service_purge_all()&lt;/tt&gt; is used then being freed. From code that entry is taken from the list without any protection, so that is possible place when it is being freed at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wasn&apos;t able to reproduce that but it seems that is only place where it can happen and solution would be just take the same spinlock &lt;tt&gt;svcpt-&amp;gt;scp_lock&lt;/tt&gt; which is used in all other place where these &lt;tt&gt;rqbd_list&lt;/tt&gt; linkage is being used&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
